 @FactualGenius  wrong. We all know MJ is the best halftime ever, but Madonna was watched by more people on this night. MJ may have been the blueprint for Madonna's show, but she was the blueprint for the MODERN 21st century Halftime show.

And also, tell me how MJ was so original and groundbreaking in his performance? He just had a body double, stood there for 2 minutes doing nothing, did Jam and Billie Jean for 3 seconds and finished with a song no one knows.

Madonna debuted a brand new song, recreated Vogue, had a martching band, full choir, cameras were HD and close to her face. Also, it's Madonna...a super girlie artist performing at the most masculine event of all time carried in my gladiators. Then flipping in high heels and singing live.

