 @codsquad3819  They don't choose at random. The Superbowl halftime show is a big deal, and preparations start a year before the show happens. They have plenty of time to curate their headliners such that there's gender equality is achieved. 

And, even if what you're saying is true, that they don't actively seek to overlook women, they need to ask themselves why women are being overlooked anyway. Does their system favour male performers? Why?

It's not good enough to just say: "That's not their intention." because the truth is that women are being overlooked, even if that 'isn't their intention'.

